{"id":550,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":550,"title":"Glory of the Lord, or of Jehovah","subtitle":"","short_title":"Glory of the Lord, or of Jehovah","uri":"/scriptures/bd/glory-of-the-lord","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/glory-of-the-lord.t1","order":".000.1433"},[".title","Glory of the Lord, or of Jehovah"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/glory-of-the-lord.p1","order":".000.1434"},"An expression that occurs frequently in the Old Testament. It sometimes denotes the fulness of the majesty of God, revealed in the world and made known to men (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/14.21-22"},"Num. 14:21–22"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/6.3"},"Isa. 6:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/66.19"},"66:19"],"); in other places it denotes some outward and visible manifestation of God’s presence (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/33.17-23"},"Ex. 33:17–23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezek/1.28"},"Ezek. 1:28"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezek/9.3"},"9:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezek/10.4,18-19"},"10:4, 18–19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezek/11.23"},"11:23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezek/43.2-5"},"43:2–5"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.9"},"Luke 2:9"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/9.32"},"9:32"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/1.14"},"John 1:14"],")."]]],"refs":null}
